OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1776877554
OL,3,CFirst Minister welcomes dismissal of
OL,4,Clegal challenge to Irish language
OL,5,Cpolicy
OL,7,F"And I think that what we need to see
OL,8,Fnow, instead of the minister chasing
OL,9,Fcourt cases after trying to do down
OL,10,Fthe Irish language, what we need to
OL,11,Fsee is a minister, actually, who is
OL,12,Fresponsible for promotion of the
OL,13,Flanguage to get on with delivering an
OL,14,FIrish language strategy."
OL,16,FThe draft Irish language policy has
OL,17,Fbeen paused while a "callin
OL,18,Fmechanism" is considered, allowing 15%
OL,19,Fof councillors to seek further
OL,20,Fscrutiny and legal advice on potential
OL,21,Fadverse impacts on one community.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@YO]yD@UOUzD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/7
